{
  "texts": [
    "Assign sentiment scores to words and calculate an overall sentiment score based on the words present in the text e.g., Lexicon-Based Approaches (e.g., using sentiment lexicons like HowNet, National Taiwan University Sentiment Dictionary (NTUSD), and WordNet) and Rule-based approaches (e.g., defining rules based on linguistic patterns) Simple to implement, interpretable, can handle domain-specific sentiment, and work well for short texts • Limited Capability for Complex Text Handling: Lexicon-based methods often struggle with understanding context.",
    "Texts with ambiguous or multi-meaning words can confuse the lexicon-based approach • Challenges arise when handling extensive amounts of text data, particularly with sentences and paragraphs.",
    "The method might falter in comprehending complex semantic contexts and implicit sentiment expressions within lengthy texts • Difficulty in Capturing Diverse Expressions: The method's coverage of sentiment expressions may be restricted, especially in discerning nuances like sarcasm and contextual variations Traditional machine learning algorithms (Yan et al.",
    "2014; Tan and Zhang 2008; Wang and Parth 2016; Qiang et al.",
    "2005; Wan 2011; Li and Sun 2007; Wang et al."
  ]
}